Type: Package
Package: jeopardyNLP
Title: Analyze Jeopardy! Clue Text with NLP Techniques
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Chris Reger
Maintainer: Chris Reger <kcr28@nau.edu>
Description: Provides functions and workflows for preprocessing,
    exploring, and modeling text data from Jeopardy! clues. Includes tools
    for text cleaning, exploratory data analysis (EDA) via word clouds and
    plots, unsupervised topic modeling using Non-negative Matrix
    Factorization (NMF), and supervised classification of clue difficulty.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: R (>= 3.5)
Imports: dplyr, forcats, ggplot2, lifecycle, Matrix, NMF, RColorBrewer,
        readr, scales, slam, stringr, tm, tidyr, wordcloud
Suggests: caret, e1071, here, knitr, purrr, rmarkdown, SnowballC,
        testthat (>= 3.0.0), textstem, tibble
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
LazyDataCompression: xz
